      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is incredibly exhausting to feel like time has stopped and that your efforts no longer matter, especially when you are grieving a loss that feels so final. Please remember that healing after something this profound is not about \"getting better\" or moving on quickly, but simply about allowing yourself to exist in the pain without needing to fix it right away. You deserve to feel whatever you are feeling, even if it feels pointless, because your presence still matters in the world.",
